{"id":25763,"date":"2021-12-23T09:34:09","date_gmt":"2021-12-23T14:34:09","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/blog-v2.sweeten.com\/?p=25763"},"modified":"2023-11-22T04:02:58","modified_gmt":"2023-11-22T09:02:58","slug":"brooklyn-brownstone-renovation-part-3","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/sweeten-renovations\/entire-home-renovations\/brooklyn-brownstone-renovation-part-3\/","title":{"rendered":"My Sweeten Story: A Brooklyn Townhouse Works for Everyone"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<h2 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">A top floor holds a playroom, an extra powder room, and a couple&#8217;s lounge<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span class=\"s1\"><b><\/b><\/span><span class=\"s2\"><b><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-31.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-44056\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-31.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-31-600x400.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-31-300x200.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/b><\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"s2\"><b>Homeowners:<\/b> Part 3 of\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/app.sweeten.com\/projects\/3494\"><span class=\"s3\">Nazli and Larry\u2019s <\/span><\/a>complete gut and remodel of their Brooklyn brownstone (Read Part <a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/sweeten-renovations\/family-renovates-brooklyn-brownstone\/\"><span class=\"s3\">1<\/span><\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/sweeten-renovations\/entire-home-renovations\/brooklyn-brownstone-sets-modern-living\/\"><span class=\"s3\">2<\/span><\/a> here)<\/span><b><\/b><\/li>\n<li><span class=\"s2\"><b>Where:<\/b> Bedford-Stuyvesant, Brooklyn, New York<\/span><b><\/b><\/li>\n<li><span class=\"s2\"><b>Primary renovation:<\/b> Renovating a sunlit top floor along with a laundry and child&#8217;s room<\/span><b><\/b><\/li>\n<li><span class=\"s2\"><b>Sweeten\u2019s role:<\/b> <a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/\"><span class=\"s3\">Sweeten<\/span><\/a> matches home renovation projects with vetted general contractors, offering advice, support, and up to $50,000 in renovation financial protection\u2014for free.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul class=\"ul1\"><\/ul>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s2\"><i>Written in partnership with homeowner Nazli<\/i><\/span><\/p>\n<h3 class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s2\">A Brooklyn house vs apartment<\/span><\/h3>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s2\">Every time I tell the tale of how a room came about, it begins, \u201cThis was a big fight over\u2026.\u201d I don\u2019t know if this is true of all couples who embark on a renovation project of this scale, but both our architect and contractor said they should charge clients for marriage counseling on top of the rest of their work, so I know we\u2019re not alone.<\/span><\/p>\n<div><\/div>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-39.jpg\" alt=\"kids playroom\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-25765\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-39.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-39-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-39-600x400.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-39-723x482.jpg 723w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-39-585x390.jpg 585w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-41.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-25770\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-41.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-41-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-41-600x400.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-41-723x482.jpg 723w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-40.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1500\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-25769\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-40.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-40-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-40-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-40-723x1085.jpg 723w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Let\u2019s begin with the impetus for the whole move: our little roommate, Nacho. As far as roommates go, this one is not so bad. He\u2019s demanding and he struggles to clean up after himself, but man oh man, do we love this guy. We wanted to move into a home to give him a better sense of what it means to grow up in a community: to plant flowers in the tree pits with our neighbors, to attend block association meetings (where he gets to call the meeting to order), to hang on the stoop, meet neighbors and observe street life, and to have the space to run around and be a kid.<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">There is so much I miss about apartment living. I\u2019m a total city brat, but to see Nacho lose it when he hears birds outside or sees a squirrel running around the backyard is pretty darn amazing.<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-42.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1500\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-25768\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-42.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-42-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-42-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-42-723x1085.jpg 723w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/span><span class=\"s1\"><\/span><\/p>\n<h3 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">New life for the brownstone bedrooms<\/span><\/h3>\n<p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\">Nacho&#8217;s playroom is separated by sliding doors from a small bedroom where he sleeps. At some point, Nacho may move to the playroom, or we may convert the small bedroom to another guest bedroom or office or a nursery\u2014who knows? Point is, I like the flexibility with the two joined yet separate spaces.<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\">I <a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/gallery\/reno-notebook\/bedroom-storage-style-renovation-ideas\/\"><span class=\"s2\">love the master bedroom<\/span><\/a>. It\u2019s a good lesson on what paint can do for a room. This house taught me to go dark, and to appreciate the power of the color black. The entire room got new moldings and trim, and the original gross color on the walls was removed.<\/span><\/p>\n<blockquote><p><span>&#8220;When we realized we had this little bit of extra space in our master bedroom suite, we quickly redesigned the bathroom&#8230;&#8221;<\/span><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-24.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-25774\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-24.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-24-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-24-600x400.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-24-723x482.jpg 723w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-30.jpg\" alt=\"Brooklyn bathroom\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-25775\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-30.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-30-723x482.jpg 723w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-30-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-30-600x400.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-30-585x390.jpg 585w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/span><\/p>\n<h3 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Adding character with the color black<\/span><\/h3>\n<p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\">This Brooklyn brownstone seemed to call for darker colors. Interestingly, the black paint doesn\u2019t make the spaces feel dark or small. It makes our stairs feel like a real feature, it keeps the master bath from feeling like a blah condo bathroom, and it brings out the moldings and woodwork in our master bedroom. All of the rooms look elegant and uncluttered without feeling too stark. I\u2019m a big fan. The colors also looked really different on walls versus woodwork and depending on how the light hit it. I had to choose between 15 different shades of black.<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-31.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-25776\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-31.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-31-723x482.jpg 723w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-31-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-31-600x400.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-31-585x390.jpg 585w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-32.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1500\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-25777\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-32.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-32-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-32-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-32-723x1085.jpg 723w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/span><\/p>\n<h3 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">A luxury bathroom comes to life<\/span><\/h3>\n<p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\">The master bathroom is cool. The whole bathroom started out with the wall-mounted faucet, and I designed the rest of the bathroom around it. I love the black tile wall and the concrete and wood vanity. Our architect created great drawings for the concrete guys and carpenter to use for the vanity and countertop. We saved a bit by using a beautiful teak veneer rather than solid teak.<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\">Design around who you are and how you behave. I realized that I was often late in the mornings because Larry would take forever in the bathroom. When we realized we had this little bit of extra space in our master bedroom suite, we quickly redesigned the bathroom, giving ourselves a long vanity with a single sink (I\u2019d rather have more counter space), and created this little toilet room with its own sink.<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-33.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1500\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-25779\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-33.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-33-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-33-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-33-723x1085.jpg 723w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-34-35.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"723\" height=\"1085\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-25780\" \/><\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-18.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1500\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-25783\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-18.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-18-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-18-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-18-723x1085.jpg 723w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/span><\/p>\n<h3 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The well-located laundry room<\/span><\/h3>\n<p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\">Let\u2019s get to the Real Housewives of Brooklyn\u2014all we ever wanted was a laundry room that\u00a0wasn\u2019t tucked away in a creepy 200-year-old basement. After the dining room, this might be my favorite room in the house. I think that architecture directs behavior. When the laundry room is conveniently located, everyone does their laundry in a timely manner. It\u2019s less about a love of doing laundry, which I obviously hate doing, and more about having a great appreciation for setting up a space where it can be done efficiently and where towels and sheets can be stored right away after folding.<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-19.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1500\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-25784\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-19.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-19-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-19-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-19-723x1085.jpg 723w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-36-38.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-25786\" \/><\/span><\/p>\n<h3 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">A man cave full of light<\/span><\/h3>\n<p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\">Larry was so excited to have his own office\u2014formerly a bathroom\u2014and couldn\u2019t be happier with the setup. Everything is within arm\u2019s reach, and there is enough built-in storage for his books and files. When we are running around in the house, he can shut the sliding doors and have his cave, while still allowing light in from the skylights because of the lovely <a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/ideas-and-inspiration\/transom-windows-let-the-light-in\/\"><span class=\"s2\">transom windows we built in<\/span><\/a>. Our architect did a great job with the layout upstairs to ensure maximum light.<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-21.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-25785\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-21.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-21-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-21-600x400.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/07\/SWEETEN_Nazli_Apartment-21-723x482.jpg 723w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Our lounge is outside of Larry\u2019s office, and it\u2019s our Friday night hangout. At the end of every week, we like to tuck Nacho into bed and crawl on the couch to watch a movie. We\u2019ve never made it past the first 15 minutes without falling asleep. Nevertheless, we love having a space just for us.<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Larry likes having the doors to his office open and being able to watch a game while he works late into the night. The ability to open his office up to the lounge allows a lot of flexibility in the space, both now and in the future. We love that there\u2019s no door to the lounge; it means stepping into a very open space as soon as you get to the top of the stairs.<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">I\u2019m going to acknowledge that we are fortunate as New Yorkers to be able to afford and renovate this Brooklyn brownstone. It allowed us access to capital, insurance, and <a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/renovation-101\/reno-101\/mortgage-101-everything-need-home-loans\/\"><span class=\"s2\">loans<\/span><\/a> not available to most of our neighbors who were in fact systematically denied loans. I am aware that other people were forced to sell their homes for nothing. So while I\u2019m happy to talk about tile, we are grateful for the choices we have been afforded in life, which got us to the point where our fights are about where to put a bathtub. Speaking of which\u2026we didn\u2019t get a bathtub. It\u2019s just one of a million tiny regrets and shoulda-woulda\u2019s that are unavoidable in this process.<\/span><\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><i>Thank you to Nazli, Larry, and Nacho for generously sharing your Brooklyn brownstone!<\/i><\/span><\/p>\n<h3 class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Renovation materials<\/b><\/s